# StyleSelectionWidget Rules

## Brand kit dropdown on main widget
- Show the brand kit dropdown **only** when `selectionMode === 'brand-template'`.
- For `recent-design` and `surprise-me` modes, the dropdown is **hidden**.
  - Instead, put the "Change reference" button in the **same row as the "Visual reference" heading** (`.style-selection-widget__title-row` flex layout).

## Brand kit dropdown inside the flyout
- The "Apply Brand" tab in the flyout **does** contain a brand kit dropdown, so users can switch kits even when a recent design or Surprise me is the active selection on the main widget.
- Switching the kit inside the flyout calls the same `handleSelectBrandKit` handler, which updates `selectedBrandKitId` in App.jsx and auto-selects the first template of the new kit.
- The "Apply Brand" tab shows only the brand templates that belong to the currently selected brand kit (passed via the `templates` prop — already filtered in App.jsx).

## No auto-selection of templates — CRITICAL
- `selectedStyleTemplate` in App.jsx must NEVER be auto-set to a default template (e.g. `brandTemplates[0]`).
- It starts as `null` and only becomes non-null when the user explicitly clicks a card in the flyout.
- When switching brand kits, set `selectedStyleTemplate` to `null` (clear old selection), never auto-pick the first card of the new kit.
- The main widget preview image uses a fallback (`selected ?? visibleTemplates[0]`) so it always shows something visually — but `selected` being null means no checkmark appears in the flyout.

## Flyout selection state — CRITICAL
- When the flyout opens, it **must** sync its active tab to `selectionMode`:
  - `'brand-template'` → open on `'apply-brand'` tab
  - `'recent-design'`  → open on `'use-recent'` tab
  - `'surprise-me'`   → open on `'surprise-me'` tab
- Inside the flyout, **only** the item that is currently selected on the **main widget** (`selected` prop) may have a checkmark. All other items must be unchecked.
- The `isSelected` check for brand templates: `selectionMode === 'brand-template' && selected?.id === tpl.id`
- The `isSelected` check for recent designs: `selectionMode === 'recent-design' && selected?.id === design.id`
- Never use a fallback that marks items selected based on index or list position.
- Never persist the last flyout tab across open/close cycles; always re-derive it from `selectionMode` on open.

## Selecting an item from the flyout
- Selecting a brand template sets `selectionMode = 'brand-template'` and closes the flyout.
- Selecting a recent design sets `selectionMode = 'recent-design'` and closes the flyout.
- Clicking "Got it!" in the Surprise me tab sets `selectionMode = 'surprise-me'` and closes the flyout.
